  "acceptance_criteria": [
    "Provide a lightweight, dismissible player guidance path for first objective, select district, inspect district, appointment/governance action, observe result, and next-step feedback.",
    "Guidance uses existing read models, command previews, accepted tutorial/hint/encyclopedia evidence, and localized player text; it does not create a full new tutorial system.",
    "Guidance must not force irreversible player decisions, submit commands without confirmation, hide command costs, or privilege player-only behavior over the AI command surface.",
    "Guidance surfaces no raw debug labels, raw IDs, state hash, revision, raw reason code, milestone label, or prototype text in player mode.",
    "Historical/cultural wording uses accepted review status and routes unresolved culture-specific wording or symbols to historical_researcher or Human Gate.",
    "Core guidance path has Storybook and Playwright or equivalent e2e coverage in English, Simplified Chinese, and system fallback."
  ],
